The roads are steep and narrow and not paved.

257
00:16:58,129 --> 00:17:01,129
Maybe you could solve that problem.

258
00:17:01,129 --> 00:17:03,129
But I'm afraid of the steep slopes.

259
00:17:03,129 --> 00:17:06,129
So that means no.

260
00:17:06,129 --> 00:17:10,129
I don't think your question came without a reason.

261
00:17:10,129 --> 00:17:13,129
Yes, unfortunately. You know...

262
00:17:13,129 --> 00:17:16,129
Oh, let's leave it at that.

263
00:17:17,129 --> 00:17:19,129
Okay.

264
00:17:19,363 --> 00:17:22,363
Yes, that's it, that's it.

265
00:17:22,363 --> 00:17:23,363
What?

266
00:17:23,363 --> 00:17:26,363
Didn't you say you were going to the mountains earlier?

267
00:17:26,363 --> 00:17:27,363
Me?

268
00:17:27,363 --> 00:17:28,363
Yes, me.

269
00:17:28,363 --> 00:17:29,363
It doesn't matter.

270
00:17:29,363 --> 00:17:31,363
The main thing is that you're leaving tomorrow.

271
00:17:31,363 --> 00:17:32,363
Tomorrow?

272
00:17:32,363 --> 00:17:34,363
Yes, someone has to check how Heidi is doing.

273
00:17:34,363 --> 00:17:35,363
You want to go on vacation.

274
00:17:35,363 --> 00:17:36,363
You said that yourself.

275
00:17:36,363 --> 00:17:39,363
So what does that mean that you're going to the mountains?

276
00:17:39,363 --> 00:17:41,363
And that's best tomorrow.

277
00:17:41,363 --> 00:17:43,363
I haven't decided yet.

278
00:17:43,849 --> 00:17:45,849
But, Mr. Secret, I don't understand you.

279
00:17:45,849 --> 00:17:48,849
Earlier, you were like a schoolboy from the mountains, and now you're in a
hurry.

280
00:17:48,849 --> 00:17:49,849
Yes, but...

281
00:17:49,849 --> 00:17:50,849
No buts.

282
00:17:50,849 --> 00:17:52,849
I promised Clara that she could visit Heidi.

283
00:17:52,849 --> 00:17:54,849
And you have to keep promises.

284
00:17:56,849 --> 00:17:57,849
But no!

285
00:17:58,849 --> 00:18:00,849
Mr. Zesemann!

286
00:18:01,849 --> 00:18:02,849
Clara?

287
00:18:02,849 --> 00:18:04,849
Papa! Oh, good afternoon.

288
00:18:04,849 --> 00:18:05,849
Good afternoon.

289
00:18:05,849 --> 00:18:07,849
I have a message for you that will make you happy.

290
00:18:07,849 --> 00:18:09,849
We have come up with a solution.

291
00:18:09,849 --> 00:18:10,849
He drives up and watches everything.

292
00:18:10,849 --> 00:18:11,849
But no!

293
00:18:12,366 --> 00:18:16,166
The secret council? No, I have not yet decided on that.

294
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:22,166
Oh yes, don't worry, he's driving. He will visit Heidi and her grandfather and
see if you can go.

295
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:24,666
Well, what do you say to that? Nothing yet.

296
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:31,166
Clara Sesemann, now you disappoint me again. I expected you to be happy and what
do you do? A sad face.

297
00:18:31,766 --> 00:18:36,766
Yes. And if he doesn't like it up there, what then?

298
00:18:38,566 --> 00:18:41,966
You see? Then I'm not allowed to drive, that's what you mean.

299
00:18:42,302 --> 00:18:44,302
But I want to see Heidi.

300
00:18:44,302 --> 00:18:46,302
We've already noticed something.

301
00:18:50,302 --> 00:18:52,302
Clara, please believe me.

302
00:18:52,302 --> 00:18:56,302
I can understand that you're disappointed now, but have patience.

303
00:18:56,302 --> 00:18:57,302
Always patience.

304
00:18:57,302 --> 00:19:01,302
At the moment it's just about finding a proper accommodation for you.

305
00:19:02,302 --> 00:19:05,302
I can't send you to the mountains from today to tomorrow.

306
00:19:05,302 --> 00:19:07,302
We have to meet for preparations.

307
00:19:07,302 --> 00:19:10,302
That's just another excuse.

308
00:19:10,430 --> 00:19:12,430
Excuse me, Mr. Secret Service.

309
00:19:12,430 --> 00:19:14,430
Please find a way, okay?

310
00:19:14,430 --> 00:19:16,430
Take a good look at it.

311
00:19:16,430 --> 00:19:18,430
You have to tell me what it looks like.

312
00:19:18,430 --> 00:19:21,430
I want to know if it really is what Heidi has always described it as.

313
00:19:21,430 --> 00:19:24,430
But before you go, please come here again.

314
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:26,430
I would like to give you presents.

315
00:19:26,430 --> 00:19:29,430
I know exactly what you all want from Heidi.

316
00:19:29,430 --> 00:19:32,430
Grandfather likes tobacco for the pipe.

317
00:19:32,430 --> 00:19:34,430
All right, pack everything.

318
00:19:34,430 --> 00:19:36,430
I will greet you and give it to you.

319
00:19:36,430 --> 00:19:38,430
Yes, please.

320
00:19:38,702 --> 00:19:41,702
Heidi will be sad that I can't come with you.

321
00:19:41,702 --> 00:19:44,702
Please tell her that I haven't forgotten her.

322
00:19:44,702 --> 00:19:47,702
Explain to her that it's not my fault. I'd like to come.

323
00:19:47,702 --> 00:19:51,702
I'll do that. She'll certainly understand.

324
00:19:51,702 --> 00:19:55,702
She's my girlfriend.

325
00:19:55,702 --> 00:19:58,702
Don't cry.

326
00:19:58,702 --> 00:20:02,702
I'm already curious what you're going to tell her.

327
00:20:02,702 --> 00:20:05,702
I like you better this way, Clara.

328
00:20:05,702 --> 00:20:08,702
You're laughing again.

329
00:20:08,846 --> 00:20:11,846
Herr Geheimrat, packen Sie.

330
00:20:11,846 --> 00:20:13,846
Ja, gut.

331
00:20:13,846 --> 00:20:17,846
Ich werde Fräulein Rottenmeier zu dir schicken, damit ihr gleich die Geschenke
besprechen könnt.

332
00:20:17,846 --> 00:20:21,846
Ja, und sie soll den größten Koffer vom Dachboden holen.

333
00:20:21,846 --> 00:20:41,846
Guten Morgen, hat dir der Postbote heute einen Brief mitgegeben?

334
00:20:41,846 --> 00:20:43,846
Ja!

335
00:20:43,846 --> 00:20:45,752
Endlich, sie hat geschrieben.

336
00:20:45,752 --> 00:20:48,752
Clara wrote me a letter, hopefully a long one.

337
00:20:48,752 --> 00:20:49,752
Morning.

338
00:20:51,752 --> 00:20:53,752
If you say it again, I'm talking nonsense.

339
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:55,752
I won't say it today, but don't you want your letter?

340
00:20:55,752 --> 00:20:57,752
Is it a long one?

341
00:20:57,752 --> 00:20:58,752
I don't know.

342
00:20:58,752 --> 00:21:00,752
Show it to me, we'll open it.

343
00:21:01,752 --> 00:21:04,752
Oh Peter, I've been waiting for it for so long.

344
00:21:04,752 --> 00:21:05,752
You can probably say that.

345
00:21:05,752 --> 00:21:07,752
Yes, I know.

346
00:21:08,323 --> 00:21:12,323
My dear friend Heidi, thank you very much for the many letters.

347
00:21:12,323 --> 00:21:15,323
How are you? I'm fine. There's something new.

348
00:21:15,323 --> 00:21:18,323
The Herr Geheimrat is coming to you in the mountains.

349
00:21:18,323 --> 00:21:21,323
Clara is coming with the Geheimrat! Grandfather!

350
00:21:21,323 --> 00:21:25,323
Clara is writing that she is coming to visit us with the Geheimrat.

351
00:21:25,379 --> 00:21:31,619
I've already packed all the presents. A warm winter coat for you and a scarf for
Peter's grandmother.

352
00:21:31,619 --> 00:21:33,619
And tobacco for your grandfather.

353
00:21:33,619 --> 00:21:37,879
And because you told me that Peter likes to eat, I've also packed sausages.

354
00:21:37,879 --> 00:21:38,879
That's good.

355
00:21:38,879 --> 00:21:39,879
Oh.

356
00:21:39,879 --> 00:21:42,879
They taste good. They're different from the ones we always eat here.

357
00:21:42,879 --> 00:21:44,379
Yes, do you mean that?

358
00:21:44,379 --> 00:21:46,879
Many, maybe even...

359
00:21:46,879 --> 00:21:48,879
A whole suitcase full!

360
00:21:48,879 --> 00:21:50,379
A suitcase!

361
00:21:50,379 --> 00:21:54,379
But doesn't she give him everything at once, or does he eat them all at once?

362
00:21:54,659 --> 00:21:55,859
That's what it says.

363
00:21:55,859 --> 00:21:57,259
Of course it says that.

364
00:21:57,259 --> 00:22:00,059
Do you think I came up with that?

365
00:22:00,059 --> 00:22:03,259
Don't give him everything at once, or he'll eat them all at once.

366
00:22:03,259 --> 00:22:04,259
That's what it says.

367
00:22:04,259 --> 00:22:07,659
You can check it if you want, but you can't read it.

368
00:22:07,659 --> 00:22:09,459
Of course I can, but not so fast.

369
00:22:10,259 --> 00:22:13,859
I'm so happy to see you again one day, Heidi.

370
00:22:14,259 --> 00:22:18,259
And I finally want to get to know Peter and his grandfather.

371
00:22:21,059 --> 00:22:23,459
Heidi, are you finally satisfied?

372
00:22:24,467 --> 00:22:28,467
You don't know how much.

373
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:33,467
Klara, Klara, come, Klara has written, she's coming.

374
00:22:33,467 --> 00:22:36,467
Heidi had misunderstood Klara's letter.

375
00:22:36,467 --> 00:22:42,467
Maybe it was because she couldn't even imagine in her dream that Klara would not
come.

376
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:47,467
That Klara only spoke in her letter from the secret council, to which she wanted
to give gifts.

377
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:50,035
She had overread that.

378
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:57,035
Every morning, when Heidi opened her eyes, she hoped that Peter had a new letter
with him, in which Klara would announce her arrival.

379
00:22:57,035 --> 00:23:04,035
But instead of a letter, the secret council came. Peter met him one day when he
went up to the meadow with the goats.

380
00:23:04,035 --> 00:23:10,035
And after he had understood who the stranger was, he brought him to Heidi and
the Almöhi.

381
00:23:10,035 --> 00:23:15,035
Heidi was disappointed. She was angry and distressed that Klara did not come
with her.

382
00:23:15,299 --> 00:23:22,299
With the help of a milk bucket, the secret guard tried to make it clear to her
how dangerous the stay in the mountains would be for a girl in a wheelchair.

383
00:23:22,299 --> 00:23:25,299
But Heidi was not convinced so quickly.

384
00:23:25,299 --> 00:23:28,799
But we want to tell you about this in our next story.

385
00:23:28,799 --> 00:23:36,799
Heidi, Heidi, your world are the mountains.

386
00:23:36,799 --> 00:23:44,799
Heidi, Heidi, because up here you are at home.

387
00:23:44,799 --> 00:23:50,799
Heidi, Heidi, come home.

388
00:23:50,799 --> 00:23:57,799
Find your happiness, come back home.

